Quantum Mechanical Powered Engine (QMPE) - Theoretical Abstraction Topology
│
├── 1. Quantum Energy Input Layer
│   ├── Zero-Point Energy Interface
│   │   └── Harvests vacuum fluctuations from quantum fields
│   ├── Quantum Tunneling Conduits
│   │   └── Enables sub-barrier energy transmission for activation efficiency
│   └── Superposition-State Extractors
│       └── Draws power from systems in coherent multi-state energy potentials
│
├── 2. Quantum-to-Macro Energy Conversion Core
│   ├── Quantum Heat Engine Module
│   │   ├── Operates on quantized thermodynamic cycles (e.g., quantum Carnot)
│   │   └── Utilizes entangled states for synchronized energy transitions
│   ├── Vacuum Fluctuation Rectifier
│   │   └── Converts random quantum noise into usable directional force
│   └── Quantum Coherence Amplifiers
│       └── Amplify extracted energy while preserving wavefunction integrity
│
├── 3. Regulation & Control Systems
│   ├── Quantum State Stabilizer
│   │   └── Maintains coherence against decoherence and thermal noise
│   ├── Entanglement Synchronization Network
│   │   └── Aligns quantum subsystems for collective energy extraction
│   └── Dynamic State Router
│       └── Directs flow of probabilistic outputs toward propulsion phase
│
├── 4. Propulsion Output Layer
│   ├── Quantum Momentum Actuators
│   │   └── Generates thrust via engineered momentum from wavefunction collapse
│   ├── Casimir Drive Assemblies
│   │   └── Exploits pressure differentials in vacuum energy
│   └── Geometric Phase Thrusters
│       └── Induces movement via manipulation of quantum phase evolution
│
└── 5. Environmental and Structural Integration
    ├── Cryo-Stabilized Hull (suppress quantum noise, thermal shielding)
    ├── Supermaterial Conduits (low decoherence, high conductivity)
    └── Quantum Feedback Recycling Loop
        └── Reuses unused entangled energy states for efficiency maximization
